<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF8CEF4FFF12FBAFFEAEFB8D" box="[151,283,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,181,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-17@37.[151,1436,181,1520]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 17. Species of Phaneropterini (Phaneropterinae) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A and B: Grammadera (Deragramma) albida, male and female; C and D: G. (D.) steinbachi, male and female; E and F: G. (Grammadera) clara, male and female; G and H: Mendesius albosignatus, male and female; I: Tomeophera australis, male; J: T. modesta, male; K and L: Viadana piracicabae, male and female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550095/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 17C, D</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF8CEF4FFF12FBD7FC99FB18" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF12FBD7FC7AFBC5" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[151,975,1121,1149]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF12FBD7FE86FBC4" bold="true" box="[151,307,1122,1148]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution:</emphasis>
Argentina: Misiones; Bolivia: Santa Cruz; 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFC9CFBD7FCD7FBC4" bold="true" box="[793,866,1122,1148]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF8CEF4FFC9CFBD7FCD7FBC4" box="[793,866,1122,1148]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFCF4FBD4FC7DFBC4" bold="true" box="[881,968,1121,1148]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF8CEF4FFCF4FBD4FC7DFBC4" box="[881,968,1121,1148]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Paraná</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FB33FC99FB18" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[199,812,1157,1184]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FB33FC99FB18" bold="true" box="[199,812,1157,1184]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
New record for the 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF8CEF4FFE2AFB33FE4DFB18" box="[431,504,1158,1184]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF8CEF4FFD0FFB30FC92FB18" box="[650,807,1157,1184]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF8CEF4FFF42FB1FFC8EFA5D" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FB1FFE43FB51" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FB1FFEE7FB7C" bold="true" box="[199,338,1194,1220]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Comments:</emphasis>
The species was recently recorded in southern of 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF8CEF4FFC01FB1FFBD8FB7C" box="[900,1133,1194,1220]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Santa Cruz Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF8CEF4FFBFCFB1FFB7BFB7C" box="[1145,1230,1194,1220]" name="Bolivia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, closer to the Brazilian border (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF8CEF4FFEB3FB7BFE5FFB51" author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[310,490,1230,1257]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="135 - 157" refId="ref32707" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2016) Systematics of the American katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Communication 6. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 320 (2), 135 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2016.320.2.135" type="journal article" year="2016">Gorochov 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FB47FCC4FAEC" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FB47FEEEFAB4" bold="true" box="[199,347,1266,1292]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF8CEF4FFEEFFB47FE45FAB5" box="[362,496,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[208,1382,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-29@38.[200,1387,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 18. Calling songs of the species of Phaneropterini species from the ParNa Iguaçu. A–F: Anaulacomera argentina; C–E: Grammadera albida; F–H: Grammadera steinbachi. A, C and D: sonogram of one echeme, two and three isolated syllables, respectively; B, D and G: sonogram of a syllable; F, E and H: spectrogram of the respective syllable." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550097/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 18 G–I</figureCitation>
): The stridulation is performed during the day and also at the beginning of the night. Males produce echemes of short duration, each one formed by two syllables. The syllables present a common crescendo until reaching the peak that is followed by a decrescendo.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FAEAFDE1FAC0" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[199,596,1374,1401]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FAEAFE1EFAC0" box="[199,427,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 27 ± 0.5 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FA37FE45FA24" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[199,496,1410,1437]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FA37FEF5FA24" box="[199,320,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 5.3 ± 0.5 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FA12FCB1FA79" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[199,772,1446,1473]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FA12FE9BFA78" box="[199,302,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Duration</emphasis>
: Syllable: 16 ± 2 ms; Echeme: 47 ± 4 ms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8CEF4FFF42FA7EFC8EFA5D" blockId="36.[151,1437,1121,1509]" box="[199,827,1482,1509]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8CEF4FFF42FA7EFEEAFA5C" box="[199,351,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 15 ± 2 ms; Echeme: 0.7 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF8CEF4FFD7AFA7FFC83FA5D" box="[767,822,1482,1509]" degrees="0.2" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="5555" value="-0.2">0.2 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
